In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims June 2013 as National Oceans Month. He emphasizes the critical role that oceans play in various aspects of national life, such as providing food, energy, and supporting transportation and trade networks. The President acknowledges the importance of managing oceans, coasts, and the Great Lakes wisely to ensure their cleanliness and productivity for future generations. He highlights the need to address threats like overfishing, pollution, and climate change. The Obama Administration has developed a plan to turn the National Ocean Policy into concrete actions that protect the environment, streamline federal operations, and promote economic growth. The plan emphasizes science and data sharing, reducing duplication, and empowering communities to bring local solutions. The President calls upon Americans to take action to protect, conserve, and restore the oceans, coasts, and the Great Lakes.